Ask HN: State of malware in 2022? Share your stories
text:
Hi HN,

Have you had to deal with malware in recent times (last couple of years)? Family devices or at the workplace? Run-of-the-mill ransomware or more advanced attacks? Were they easy to deal with?

I can't recall the last time I have seen an active infection. Probably back in 2003 or so. Share your stories!

Tell HN: Facebook app external browser preference reset
text:
A few days ago the Facebook app on my (Android) phone stopped opening links in Firefox (again). The preference which used to tell it to do so was reset. After reading things like https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=32415470 it's no longer possible to believe it wasn't done on purpose.

PS My opinion is that Facebook (and any other app) should have never been allowed to have an "internal" browser.
